    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5b2072b5_a2dbc475",
        "filename": "logdog/appengine/coordinator/endpoints/services/scheduleArchiveTask.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 48,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003190
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-12-12T20:24:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Unrelated to this CL:\n\nAlthough this name is used elsewhere currently in LogDog, it\u0027s a pretty confusing name.\n\n`lst` looks like `1st`, and it also looks like an abbreviation of \"list\".\n\nPossible alternative names: `stream`. Or if we want to stick with 1-3 letter abbreviations, `lss` or `ss` might be better than lst. If you do think this could be renamed, then it could perhaps be renamed elsewhere in a separate CL.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 48,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 48,
        "endChar": 4
      },
      "revId": "a1e3b995ee157d86aa5e66ee6937f3f48c9c6da2",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "dfa38586_4c64dd74",
        "filename": "logdog/appengine/coordinator/endpoints/services/scheduleArchiveTask.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 48,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-12-15T00:21:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "by convention, \"ls\" stands for log stream, and \"lst\" stands for \"log stream state\", since they are two different entities (but 1:1 relation).\n\nI think ls -\u003e stream, and lst -\u003e state makes sense.  wdyt?",
      "parentUuid": "5b2072b5_a2dbc475",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 48,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 48,
        "endChar": 4
      },
      "revId": "a1e3b995ee157d86aa5e66ee6937f3f48c9c6da2",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
