    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "214bdb68_3ef951eb",
        "filename": "logdog/appengine/coordinator/endpoints/services/scheduleArchiveTask.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 74,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-12-12T20:20:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think you need to actually run this mutation in this handler; that way you can immediately check to see that the old key is still active. If it\u0027s not active, you return 200. Otherwise you do the transaction to CAS(oldkey, newkey). The archive task will retry this operation until it gets a 200. If the archiver dies, pubsub will re-deliver the task with the old key, and it can continue to try the reschedule (or get 200 that it was successful).\n\nIf you only post the new mutation, you could potentially have a bunch of retries on this handler from the archiver which all try to overwrite the mutation with old_key.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 74,
        "startChar": 24,
        "endLine": 74,
        "endChar": 48
      },
      "revId": "a1e3b995ee157d86aa5e66ee6937f3f48c9c6da2",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
